    h3 Accessing Ogre using a POST request
    p You can perform Ogre transformations directly by making a HTTP POST request:
    p: b Convert to GeoJSON
    code http://ogre.adc4gis.com/convert</code> with the following params:
    ul
      li <code>upload</code> - the file being uploaded
      li <code>sourceSrs</code> (optional) - the original projection
      li <code>targetSrs</code> (optional) - the target projection
      li <code>forcePlainText</code> (optional) - force `text/plain` instead of `application/json`
      li <code>skipFailures</code> (optional) - skip failures
      li <code>callback</code> (optional) - a JSONP callback function name

    p: b Convert from GeoJSON to Shapefile (or specified format)
    p: code http://ogre.adc4gis.com/convertJson</code> with <b>one of the following</b> params:
    ul
      li <code>json</code> - text of the GeoJSON file
      li <code>jsonUrl</code> - the URL for a remote GeoJSON file
      li <code>outputName</code> (optional) - the name for the resulting zip file
      li <code>skipFailures</code> (optional) - skip failures
      li <code>format</code> (optional) - File format supported by the <a href="https://github.com/wavded/ogr2ogr">ogr2ogr wrapper</a>

